sentence: Thursday's session closes with the NASDAQ Composite Index at 5,306.85.
The total shares traded for the NASDAQ was over 1.63 billion.
Declining stocks led advancers by 1.52 to 1 ratio.
There were 1135 advancers and 1730 decliners for the day.
On the NASDAQ Stock Exchange 43 stocks reached a 52 week high and 22 reaching lows.
The most active, advancers, decliners, unusual volume and most active by dollar volume can be monitored intraday on the Most Active Stocks page.
The NASDAQ 100 index closed down -.08% for the day; a total of -3.83 points.
Tesla Motors, Inc. ( TSLA ) had the largest percent change down (-3.58%) while Whole Foods Market, Inc. ( WFM ) had the largest percent change gain rising 4.9%.
The Dow Jones index closed down -.07% for the day; a total of -12.53 points.
American Express Company ( AXP ) had the largest percent change down (-3.76%) while Home Depot, Inc. (The) ( HD ) had the largest percent change gain rising 2.05%.
